Initial receipt date: 11-MAY-2015
This information was received from a literature article concerning a patient of unknown age and gender who 
received Efavirenz and Zidovudine plus Lamivudine for HIV 1 infection. 
No relevant medical history, concurrent diseases and concomitant medications were reported.
In this open-label trial, HIV-1-infected patients with a CD4 plus cell count lower than 100 cells/ml were randomly 
assigned to receive an NNRTI-based antiretroviral regimen or a boosted PI-based regimen. Eligible patients were 
randomly assigned in a 1:1 ratio to receive zidovudine (ZDV, 300mg bid) plus lamivudine (3TC, 150mg bid) 
